commitResults.messageTitle: Add Animal class and its attributes.
commitResults.messageBody:
This is part of the refactoring to our tP direction, where we want to
store animal details in the AddressBook rather than Person.
As such, the usage of Person will progressively be replaced with
completed implementation of Animal.

NOTE: The attributes of Animal are mostly incomplete as of this commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add get_ForSerialization() methods in Animal model
commitResults.messageBody:
These methods returns the appropriate string that can be serialized, or
deserialized by Jackson, without loss of information.

Rather than directly calling the toString methods of each attribute
directly, implementing separate getter methods help to improve
separation of concern. This allows the toString methods, which are
primarily used for readability, to be maintained separately from the
get_ForSerialization methods.

This class adapts Animal model such that it can be
serialized/deserialized by Jackson easily.

NOTE: Should there be any modifications to Animal model, developers must
also consider updating JsonAdaptedAnimal.

commitResults.messageBody:
Sex::toString returns 'Male' / 'Female' instead of 'M' / 'F'.
This change was made because the UI has enough space to accomodate the
full string representation, and because M/F was unintuitive.

- Add StringUtil::toTitleCase and relevant test cases.

- Changed from 'catalogFilePath' to 'animalCatalogFilePath'.

NOTE: This affects how Jackson serializes/deserializes the attribute. By
default, the key of the attribute in the Json form will be the name of
the field.

- These attributes are not planned to be implemented. Although it would
